title: Matthew Timoko
text:
Matthew Timoko (born 18 January 2000) is a professional <a href="rugby%20league">rugby league</a> <a href="footballer">footballer</a> who plays as a for the <a href="Canberra%20Raiders">Canberra Raiders</a> in the <a href="National%20Rugby%20League">NRL</a>.
Background.
Timoko was born in <a href="Auckland">Auckland</a>, <a href="New%20Zealand">New Zealand</a> and is of <a href="M%C4%81ori%20people">Māori</a> descent.
Career.
2020.
Timoko made his NRL debut in round 16 of the <a href="2020%20NRL%20season">2020 NRL season</a> for the Canberra against the <a href="Canterbury-Bankstown%20Bulldogs">Canterbury-Bankstown Bulldogs</a>; he replaced an injured <a href="Curtis%20Scott">Curtis Scott</a> in the 47th minute as the Canberra club won the game 34–20. 
2021.
Timoko played nine games for Canberra in the <a href="2021%20NRL%20season">2021 NRL season</a> as the club finished 10th on the table.
